This paper deals with the problem of predicting human behavior in the context of self-driving vehicles, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed method involves the use of a neural network, which is a common tool in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses the use of natural language processing techniques to evaluate the performance of the model, which is a topic in computational linguistics (cs.CL).
